/design-tokens/#spacing-sections.description: Padding is intrinsically applied to the top and bottom of sections. This spacing accounts for sections that have classes for curves and/or background colors as well.

/design-tokens/#spacing-sections.characteristic: [Mobile Responsive] Padding applied to section tags are responsive. Target screen-sizes using [sm|md|lg|xl].
[Background Colors] Values for [--sect-bg--] are applied to HTML sections that match the selector `section[class*=bg]`
[Curves] Values for [--sect-[top-curv|btm-curv]--] are applied to HTML sections that match the selector `section[class*=top-curv]` or `section[class*=btm-curv]`

/design-tokens/#spacing-gutters.description: Gutters are a layout mechanic that are most commonly applied to columns `col` within a grid system to keep the space left and right of an element consistent.

/design-tokens/#spacing-gutters.characteristic: [Mobile Responsive] Gutters are applied to columns `col` as margin left and right. This spacing scales with the viewport and is applied with [sm|md|lg|xl]

/design-tokens/#spacing-columns.description: Margins are instrinsically applied to the top and bottom of columns.

/design-tokens/#spacing-columns.characteristic: [Mobile Responsive] Margin top and bottom are applied to columns `col` and this spacing scales with the viewport

/design-tokens/#typography-headings-and-.description: Margins are instrinsically applied to the top and bottom of columns.

/design-tokens/#typography-headings-and-.characteristic: [Mobile Responsive] Margin top and bottom are applied to columns `col` and this spacing scales with the viewport

/css-framework/#sections.description: The section tag, while not custom, is the base element of the framework. Sections provide intrinsic padding, denotes as external spacing, to visually separate sections of a page. Additionally, sections act as a base for background color and curves.

/css-framework/#sections.characteristic: [width] Sections span full-width of the viewport
[horizontal-spacing] Sections maintain a left and right gutter on all view ports, though it is most prominent on screen-sizes below the maximum container width
[vertical-spacing] Vertical spacing on a section and between two sections is affected by background-color, curves, and whether the section is first or the last of its type on the page
[background-color] When a background colors are applied to a section, the back
[curves] Curves can be applied to the top and bottom of a section individually or simultaneously
[border-bottom] A bottom border can be applied to a `container` within a `section` using .bdr-bottom on the section

/css-framework/#content-container.description: Containers sit directly within a `section` tag helping content editors control the maximum horizontal width their content will be displayed.

/css-framework/#content-container.tags: content-width, content, width, container, max-width, layout

/css-framework/#flex-grid-row.description: Nested within a `.container` or a `.col` (column), rows are encapsulates columns for the purpose of negating the far left and far right padding or gutter of the first and last columns

/css-framework/#flex-grid-row.characteristic: [horizontal-spacing] Rows have negative margins on the left and right
[vertical-spacing] By design rows do not have margins on the top or bottom. This is enforced by !important.
[background-color] When background colors are applied to a row margin left and right are set to 0

/css-framework/#flex-grid-columns.description: Nested within a `.row`, columns generally encapsulate all content and provide horizontal padding (gutters) which are permuted at various breakpoints: sm, md, lg, and xl

/css-framework/#flex-grid-columns.characteristic: [horizontal-spacing] Columns possess padding left and right that is exactly half of the intended gutter width
